Example
Get the total height of your screen:

Copy
let x = "Total Height: " + screen.height;

Description
The height property returns the total height of the user's screen, in pixels.

We can use the width property to get the total width of the user's screen.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
height	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
let a = screen.height;
Return Value
A Number, representing the total height of the user's screen, in pixels
